<HEADLINE> Nicolas Cage's Bentley Crashed Into </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BURBANK, Calif. (AP) -- Nicolas Cage was unhurt after his  
chauffeur-driven Bentley got into a fender-bender. 
</P>
<P>
	The actor was riding in the car on Hollywood Way at about 4 p.m.  
Thursday when a teen-ager in a Toyota turned in front of the car, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
	``She cut in front of him and it went crunch,'' police Lt. Joe  
Latta said. 
</P>
<P>
	The other driver also escaped injury. No charges were  
immediately filed. 
</P>
<P>
	Cage, who won an Oscar for ``Leaving Las Vegas,'' currently  
stars in ``Bringing Out The Dead,'' a movie about New York City 
paramedics. 
  	   	
</P>
