<DOCNO> APW19991015.0013 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 13:30:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> political </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Bauer: Forbes' Bid Has 'Peaked Out' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- Publisher Steve Forbes' bid for the  
Republican presidential nomination has ``peaked out'' and has gone 
as far as his personal fortune can take it, rival Gary Bauer said 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	``He has spent $65 million since 1996 and ... he's basically in  
a dead heat with me in the polls,'' Bauer said at a news 
conference. ``I don't think money can buy him any more support than 
it already has and conservatives will continue to consolidate 
behind my candidacy.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Bauer opened his latest campaign swing by announcing the backing  
of three key conservative leaders in the state where precinct 
caucuses launch the nominating season, and by making the financial 
case for his campaign. 
</P>
<P>
	Bauer and Forbes are competing for the same base of social and  
religious conservatives, but the wealthy publisher argues that he 
is the only conservative with the financial resources to compete 
with Texas Gov. George W. Bush, the favorite in the race for the 
Republican presidential nomination. 
</P>
<P>
	Disclosure reports released Friday show that Bauer raised more  
than $1 million between July 1 and Sept. 30, while Forbes raised 
$1.4 million. Forbes, however, has access to his personal fortune. 
</P>
<P>
	Bauer has developed a direct-mail fund-raising operation that,  
while expensive to run, has shown an ability to generate money. He 
said that organization has been carefully crafted. 
</P>
<P>
	``We are more than competitive financially,'' Bauer said. ``I  
don't think anybody else has the kind of broad-based, campaign 
foundation I do, with 110,000 donors.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Those are generally smaller donors who can be tapped again,  
Bauer argued. 
</P>
<P>
	``As the campaign begins to pick up, we're going to be able to  
go back to those people time and time again,'' he said. ``That's 
why we spent seven months building that very substantial list of 
conservatives around America.'' 
</P>
<P>
	While Forbes has attracted some important conservatives because  
of the money he is able to bring to the race, that has slowed, 
Bauer said. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think he's already peaked out,'' said Bauer.  
</P>
<P>
	Bauer, meanwhile, named Gopal Krishna as his state campaign  
chairman. Krishna is a former co-chairman and treasurer of the Iowa 
Republican Party, and a significant financial force in GOP affairs. 
Bauer also named two state lawmakers to co-chair his campaign. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
