<HEADLINE> Williams May Start for Saints </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Earlier in the week, New Orleans Saints coach  
Mike Ditka said it might be time to allow injured running back 
Ricky Williams to heal. 
</P>
<P>
	Now, Ditka indicated Williams is likely to start against the  
Tennessee Titans on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Williams is listed as questionable with a hyperextended right  
elbow and a left ankle sprain. But he returned to practice Thursday 
at full speed after sitting out Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	``Ricky ran the best he's run in six weeks,'' Ditka said of his  
top draft pick. ``It looks very good.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Tight end Cam Cleeland also practiced after sitting out  
Wednesday with a sprained ligament in his left knee. Ditka also 
said earlier that Cleeland was doubtful for Sunday's game. 
</P>
<P>
	``It looks very good for both of them,'' Ditka said.  
</P>
<P>
	Quarterback Billy Joe Hobert, who has a bruised and pinched  
nerve in his neck and right throwing shoulder, dressed for practice 
and did some throwing. But Ditka said he's leaning towards Hobert 
as the No. 3 emergency quarterback. Ditka declined to commit to a 
starter between Billy Joe Tolliver and Danny Wuerffel. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
