<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Happyanunoit Wins Keeneland Feature </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LEXINGTON, Ky. (AP) -- Happyanunoit, a New Zealand-bred filly,  
took the lead in midstretch and then pulled away to a four-length 
win Friday in the $558,500 Vinery First Lady Stakes at Keeneland. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Brice Blanc, the 4-year-old filly moved into  
contention at the top of the stretch and charged down the middle of 
the course to catch Pleasant Temper with an eighth-of-a-mile to go. 
</P>
<P>
	Happyanunoit ran the 1 3-16 miles on a firm turf course in 1:53  
4-5 to lower the course record by two-fifths of a second. 
</P>
<P>
	Pleasant Temper, the leader for more than a mile, finished  
second in the field of nine fillies and mares. Fiji, the 7-5 
favorite, was a neck back in third. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the sixth victory in 11 career starts for Happyanunoit,  
who earned $346,270 for John Amerman and his wife. Happyanunoit, 
trained by Robert J. Frankel, has earned $662,266. 
</P>
<P>
	Happyanunoit paid $7.40, $4.20 and $3. Pleasant Temper, ridden  
by Pat Day, returned $4.20 and $2.60, while Fiji, ridden by Jerry 
Bailey, paid $2.40 to show. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
