<HEADLINE> Chamberlain Memorial To Be in L.A. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- A memorial service for basketball great Wilt  
Chamberlain was scheduled for Saturday morning at The City of 
Angels Church of Religious Science near Marina del Rey. 
</P>
<P>
	The service was scheduled for 10 a.m.  
</P>
<P>
	A second memorial service will take place Thursday at Mount  
Carmel Baptist Church in Philadelphia, just blocks from the high 
school where Chamberlain first achieved fame on the basketball 
court. 
</P>
<P>
	The 7-foot-1 center, whose dominance changed the game, died  
Tuesday of heart failure at his Bel-Air home. He was 63. 
</P>
<P>
	Chamberlain played 14 NBA seasons with the Philadelphia (later  
San Francisco) Warriors, Philadelphia 76ers and Los Angeles Lakers. 
He won championship rings with the 76ers in 1967 and the Lakers in 
1972. 
</P>
<P>
	On March 2, 1962, in one of the most spectacular performances in  
any sport, he scored 100 points against the New York Knicks, a 
record that still stands. 
  	   	
</P>
