<HEADLINE> Oregon Suspends Starting Cornerback </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EUGENE, Ore. (AP) -- Oregon starting cornerback Tamoni Joiner has  
been suspended indefinitely for ``repeated violation of team 
rules,'' Ducks coach Mike Bellotti said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Joiner, a junior, will not play next week at Arizona, in his  
hometown of Tucson. The Ducks (3-3, 1-2 Pac-10) are idle this week. 
</P>
<P>
	Joiner also was suspended for a Sept. 11 game against Texas-El  
Paso. The reason Bellotti gave then also was unspecified violation 
of team rules. 
</P>
<P>
	Joiner started the Ducks' other five games this season,  
recording 18 tackles and leading the team with 18 pass break-ups. 
He had one interception and one fumble recovery. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
