<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine Economy Seen Weakening </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KIEV, Ukraine (AP) -- Ukraine's economy continued to show more  
signs of decline, with officials reporting today a 23.3 percent 
decrease in the country's foreign trade volume in January-August 
1999 from the same period last year. 
</P>
<P>
	The overall volume of foreign trade stood at $14.4 billion over  
the first eight months of 1999. Exports dropped 16.7 percent and 
imports went down 29.8 percent, the State Statistics Committee 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
	On Thursday, the committee announced that the former Soviet  
republic posted a 1.7 percent decline in gross domestic product in 
the first nine months of 1999 compared with the same period last 
year. 
</P>
<P>
	Ukraine has experienced a steady economic downfall since  
becoming independent in 1991, failing to implement market reforms 
fully. The economy was further hurt last year by the financial 
crisis in Russia. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
