<CATEGORY> political </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> New Hampshire Gov. To Endorse Gore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CONCORD, N.H. (AP) -- Gov. Jeanne Shaheen will endorse Vice  
President Al Gore for the Democratic presidential nomination, her 
spokeswoman says. 
</P>
<P>
	Shaheen will announce her support Monday at an event in Dover,  
Pamela Walsh said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The endorsement had been widely expected -- Shaheen's husband,  
William Shaheen, is director of Gore's New Hampshire campaign. 
</P>
<P>
	The announcement comes at a time when Gore's rival, former New  
Jersey Sen. Bill Bradley, is gaining on him in national polls and 
has pulled even with him in New Hampshire, which will hold the 
first presidential primary, on Feb. 1. 
</P>
<P>
	A CNN/Gallup/USA Today poll this week had Gore 12 percentage  
points ahead of Bradley nationally, down from a 33-point spread in 
a CNN/USA Today/Gallup poll in mid-September. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
