<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tenn. Teens Found Shot to Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JACKSON, Tenn. (AP) -- Two teen-agers were found shot to death at  
a home early Friday and police held two other young men for 
questioning. 
</P>
<P>
	No charges were filed.  
</P>
<P>
	Police said the shootings apparently occurred Thursday night or  
early Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	``The bodies were discovered inside the residence by the mother  
of one of the victims,'' police said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	The victims were identified as Jasper Williams and James Hicks,  
both 17. They were students at North Side High School in Jackson. 
</P>
<P>
	No motive for the killings had been determined, police said.  
</P>
<P>
	Officers said the bodies were found after police responded to a  
homicide call at 6:45 a.m. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
