<HEADLINE> One Dead in Mo. Hayride Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EUREKA, Mo. (AP) -- A wagon hauling participants in a hayride  
overturned Friday night, killing one passenger and injuring up to 
12 others. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities were calling it a ``mass-casualty incident,''  
meaning they feared there could be more injuries than emergency 
crews could handle. The Jefferson County Sheriff's Department 
confirmed the one fatality. 
</P>
<P>
	Between 10 and 12 people were injured. Three were in critical  
condition and one was in serious condition. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities weren't sure what caused the wagon to overturn.  
</P>
<P>
	The accident happened around 8:30 p.m. at the Rocking J. Ranch  
in High Ridge just southwest of St. Louis. 
  	   	
</P>
