<HEADLINE> Brewers Re-sign Valentin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Jose Valentin signed a one-year deal with the  
Milwaukee Brewers that likely includes a pay cut for the slumping 
shortstop. 
</P>
<P>
	Financial terms of the deal weren't disclosed, but Brewers  
general manager Dean Taylor announced Friday that the club's option 
on Valentin for the 2000 season had been restructured. Valentin, 
who turned 30 on Thursday, had an injury-plagued 1999 season and 
played in just 89 games. 
</P>
<P>
	Valentin's offensive numbers have steadily declined since 1996,  
when he batted .259 with 24 homers and 95 RBIs, all career-highs. 
He has spent his entire eight-year career with Milwaukee. 
</P>
<P>
	Last season he hit .227 and drove in 38 runs. He spent most of  
the first two months on the disabled list with a torn ligament in 
his left thumb. 
  	   	
