<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> No. 1 Kafelnikov Out at CA Trophy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	VIENNA, Austria (AP) -- Nicolas Kiefer upset top-seeded Yevgeny  
Kafelnikov 6-0, 6-4 Friday to advance to the semifinals of the 
$800,000 CA Trophy tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	With a crowd of 8,000 at Vienna's Stadthalle sports arena  
cheering him on, the 22-year-old German outclassed Kafelnikov, who 
is ranked second in the world. The victory also makes Kiefer the 
fourth German after Boris Becker, Michael Stich and Tommy Haas to 
be ranked in the Top Ten in the world. 
</P>
<P>
	``I am overjoyed,'' Kiefer said.  
</P>
<P>
	Kafelnikov started the match with three double faults. The  
Russian caved in after Kiefer's second service break gave the 
German a 3-0 lead. Kiefer needed only 19 minutes to zip through the 
first five games. 
</P>
<P>
	In the second set, Kafelnikov rallied somewhat, but Kiefer was  
able to convert on his fourth match point to post his second win 
against the Russian. 
</P>
<P>
	Also advancing to the semifinals were Roger Federer, a promising  
Swiss player, and sixth-seeded Richard Krajicek of the Netherlands. 
</P>
<P>
	Federer scored a 2-6, 6-4, 6-1 victory over Karol Kucera, who  
has a sore wrist and was forced to pull out of next week's 
tournament in Lyon, France. Federer will take his place in the 
field. 
</P>
<P>
	The 18-year-old Federer is ranked 93rd, the youngest player  
among the top 100. 
</P>
<P>
	Krajicek routed Australia's Stefan Koubek 6-2, 6-1 and will next  
play Kiefer. 
</P>
<P>
	``Krajicek served unbelievably well, and that increased the  
pressure on my own serve,'' said Koubek, who beat Goran Ivanisevic 
the day before. ``My serve today didn't go well.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
