<HEADLINE> Perfect To A Tee Favored at Laurel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAUREL, Md. (AP) -- Perfect To A Tee is the early favorite in  
what's expected to be a fast 11-horse field in Saturday's $200,000 
Maryland Million Classic at Laurel Park. 
</P>
<P>
	In a field that features such speedsters as Testafly and Fred  
Bear Claw, Perfect To A Tee trainer Mary Albert said she simply 
wants her horse, ridden by Alcibiades Cortez, to stay close enough 
to make a late run. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think there's some nice speed in there,'' Albert said.  
``We'll be sitting somewhere behind them, no doubt about that.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The 7-year old has won three of nine starts this year, and  
finished in the money in four others. 
</P>
<P>
	He beat Testafly last month at Philadelphia Park after finishing  
a distant third to him in June at Laurel, and also has split with 
Fred Bear Claw. They are two of several entrants in the talented 
field that have previously traded blows with one another. 
</P>
<P>
	``That's kind of the way all these horses are,'' Albert said.  
``They've beaten each other over the year.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Testafly finished ninth in last year's race as the 6-5 favorite  
and has won just one of his past nine races. 
</P>
<P>
	Another horse that could challenge is Fred Bear Claw, which has  
finished among the top three nine 11 times this year, including an 
August victory in an allowance at Delaware Park. In March, he won 
the $75,000 Sagamore at Laurel. 
</P>
<P>
	Warrenpeace is back again after narrowly missing a huge upset in  
last year's Classic, making up 25 lengths to finish a nose in back 
of two-time champion Algar, who is out this year with an ankle 
injury. 
</P>
<P>
	Praise Heaven, Steak Scam, Get The Picture, Monk's Falcon,  
Mary's Buckaroo and Testing complete the field for the 1 3/16-mile 
event. 
</P>
<P>
	The Maryland Million, in its 14th year, was originally  
introduced by ABC sportscaster Jim McKay as a way to promote the 
state's thoroughbred breeding industry. 
</P>
<P>
	The 11-race card also includes the Steeplechase, the Distaff  
Starter, the Lassie, the Distaff, the Oaks, the Ladies, the 
Nursery, the Turf, the Sprint and the Starter. 
  	   	
</P>
