<HEADLINE> Atkins Wins APME Photo Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) -- San Francisco Examiner photographer Lacy  
Atkins' shot of Brandi Chastain celebrating her game-winning goal 
in the final of the Women's World Cup soccer tournament was chosen 
Friday as the Member Showcase Photo of the Year at the Associated 
Press Managing Editors conference. 
</P>
<P>
	Atkins' photograph was a daily Member Showcase selection by the  
editors at the Associated Press' State Photo Center in Washington 
and later judged to be the photo of the month by a committee of 
AP-member newspaper judges under the sponsorship of APME. 
</P>
<P>
	It was chosen Photo of the Year in a separate judging by APME  
newspaper editors, who considered all 12 monthly winners. 
</P>
<P>
	The award, which includes a $1,000 cash honorarium, was  
presented at the APME annual conference in Memphis. 
</P>
<P>
	The annual competition is open to all AP member photographers  
for photos submitted to the AP on a spot basis. 
  	   	
</P>
