<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Friday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	
</P>
<P>
	Office Depot, up 1 3/8 at 10 1/2  
</P>
<P>
	The office supply retailer lost $1.07 million in the third  
quarter due to one-time merger and restructuring costs of $73.33 
million, but posted a better-than-expected operating profit. Office 
Depot is based in Delray Beach, Fla. 

</P>
<P>
	Navigant Consulting, down 3 5/16 at 38 5/8  
</P>
<P>
	The management consulting firm has decided to remain independent  
after reviewing potential merger options. Chicago-based Navigant 
had hired an adviser in early September to consider strategic 
alternatives including an acquisition by a larger firm. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	
</P>
<P>
	Sun Microsystems, up 3 5/32 at 92 9/16  
</P>
<P>
	The maker of powerful business and network computers posted a 39  
percent increase in quarterly profits, topping Wall Street 
forecasts. Sun, based in Palo Alto, Calif., said it continued to 
benefit from rising demand for its Internet computer systems. 

</P>
<P>
	Veeco Instruments, up 8 3/8 at 33  
</P>
<P>
	The supplier of tools for the data storage and semiconductor  
industries agreed to acquire Ion Tech for 1.5 million shares. Ion 
Tech, a privately held company, is expected to have 1999 sales of 
about $20 million. It has an order backlog of $17.5 million. 

</P>
<P>
	Veritas Software, up 9 5/8 at 91 3/32  
</P>
<P>
	The maker of storage management software topped Wall Street  
forecasts with its third-quarter results, reported late Thursday. 
Veritas, based in Mountain View, Calif., also announced a stock 
split and expressed confidence in analyst forecasts going forward. 

</P>
<P>
	ITC Learning, down 1 11/16 at 2 13/16  
</P>
<P>
	The training program developer warned that it expects to report  
an operating loss for the third quarter. ITC, based in Herndon, 
Va., said it had expected to close a number of deals in September 
that didn't materialize. ITC also said talks for an equity 
investment from Thomas Cressey Equity Partners have ended. 

</P>
<P>
	Youbet.com, down 1 1/2 at 5  
</P>
<P>
	The online wagering service announced it has provided company  
records in cooperation with a search warrant served by the Los 
Angeles County District Attorney. Los Angeles-based Youbet said the 
investigation involves the legality of online and telephone 
wagering within California. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
