<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Panamanian Head To Visit Clinton </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton will review plans to hand  
over the Panama Canal to Panama when that country's newly elected 
president visits the White House next week, Clinton's spokesman 
said today. 
</P>
<P>
	Mireya Moscoso will meet with Clinton on Tuesday -- their first  
face-to-face discussion since Moscoso took office Sept. 1. 
</P>
<P>
	``The meeting will cover the broad range of our excellent  
bilateral relations, including the upcoming transfer of the Panama 
Canal,'' a statement from White House press secretary Joe Lockhart 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Under a 1977 agreement, the last U.S. forces will pull out of  
Panama on Dec. 31, and control of the U.S.-built canal will cede to 
Panama. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
