<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Paxson Unveils Family Online Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- Paxson Communications is developing  
a family-friendly online Internet service and search engine that 
blocks 32 categories of pornography, violence and hate groups. 
</P>
<P>
	Paxson plans to offer Paxway, billed as ``a national clean  
Internet access kit for families,'' within the next few weeks for 
$19.95 a month. 
</P>
<P>
	The service provides Internet access while filtering out obscene  
or otherwise objectionable information from e-mail, newsgroups, 
file transfers and Web searches. 
</P>
<P>
	Paxway is enrolling members through the West Palm Beach-based  
company's Web site, www.paxtv.com. 
</P>
<P>
	The service will be primarily promoted on Pax TV, Paxson's  
television network. 
</P>
<P>
	Paxson subsidiary, Pax Internet, is working with Oslo,  
Norway-based Fast Search &AMP; Transfer to develop a search engine. Pax 
Fast &AMP; Safe Search Engine is expected to be released early next 
year. 
</P>
<P>
	``It will allow the users to search the entire World Wide Web  
and the return of the search will not have any obscene materials or 
even the headlines,'' Ben Ly, Paxson's online business development 
director, said Thursday. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
