<HEADLINE> Bob Barker Returning to CBS Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- A month after surgery cleared a blockage in  
his carotid artery, Bob Barker is heading back to ``The Price is 
Right.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The longtime game show host says he'll resume taping the show on  
Oct. 25. 
</P>
<P>
	Barker was admitted to a Washington, D.C., hospital on Sept. 16  
after complaining of fatigue and a tingling sensation in his right 
arm. After surgery, doctors recommended that Barker rest for 
several weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	``I am feeling fine and looking forward to taping the show  
again,'' Barker said in a statement Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Barker is in his 28th year as host of ``The Price is Right.''  
</P>
<P>
	The first of the new shows he will tape is scheduled to air Nov.  
19 on CBS. Shows now on the air were taped before his surgery. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
