<DOCNO> APW19991015.0215 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 17:50:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pentagon Project Workers Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- A review of work passes of employees at a  
Pentagon construction site alerted authorities to 33 illegal aliens 
who were later arrested, officials said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	The workers were arrested during a raid on the work site  
Thursday. Immigration rights groups said four of the workers had 
been released but a Pentagon spokesman could not confirm the 
account. 
</P>
<P>
	The Pentagon's Defense Protective Service notified officials at  
the Immigration and Naturalization Service ``after it was 
determined that several foreign nationals had presented fraudulent 
immigration documents to obtain building work passes,'' said Lt. 
Col. Mike Milord, a Pentagon spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
	Milord had no further details of the raid and an INS spokesman  
did not immediately return calls seeking comment. 
</P>
<P>
	Immigration rights group complained that witness accounts  
indicate Latino workers may have been separated from the crowd, 
leaving workers to wonder why they were being singled out. 
</P>
<P>
	Abel Nunez of CARECEN, a community-based immigration service  
group, said, it was seeking information ``from people that were 
present and from the different enforcement agencies to ensure that 
the civil rights of the workers were not violated.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
