<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Italy, Germany in TV Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILAN, Italy (AP) -- Italy's Mediaset company said Friday it had  
signed its deal with KirchMedia of Germany for a joint venture 
targeting TV viewers in Germany, Italy and Spain. 
</P>
<P>
	The alliance will produce, acquire and distribute films and  
shows for a potential audience it estimates at 200 million. The 
venture would use Spanish TV station Telecino and Kirch's SAT1. 
</P>
<P>
	Mediaset said terms of the final deal mirrored those announced  
in March. 
</P>
<P>
	The terms announced then said Mediaset's control group,  
Fininvest, would take a 3.19 percent stake in KirchMedia. 
</P>
<P>
	Fininvest, controlled by former Italian Premier Silvio  
Berlusconi, owns 48.4 percent of Mediaset. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
