<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-15 20:40:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Leiter Could Have Used Some Help </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Al Leiter couldn't do it all by himself.  
</P>
<P>
	Just like he has all year, he performed well in a big game, this  
time desperately trying to get the New York Mets back into the NL 
championship series. 
</P>
<P>
	He held the Atlanta Braves to just three hits and no earned runs  
in seven inning Friday night, but the Mets lost meekly 1-0 and 
trail 3-0 in the best-of-7 series, undone by sloppy fielding, 
including his own. 
</P>
<P>
	Leiter actually outpitched Tom Glavine, who allowed at least one  
runner in each of his seven innings. 
</P>
<P>
	But the Mets trailed by a run when Shawon Dunston hit for Leiter  
in the seventh, finishing his night and probably his season. 
</P>
<P>
	The pitcher put on his warmup jacket, sat on the bench in the  
Mets dugout and spit at the ground, looking like had run through 
the streets of New York in a marathon. It seemed he had left every 
drop of his energy out on the field. 
</P>
<P>
	Then Leiter turned cheerleader, clapping hands and trying to  
shout his teammates to a run after Dunston reached on a passed 
ball. 
</P>
<P>
	But the Mets didn't score then, didn't score all night long. If  
you don't get any runs, the best pitching in the world won't win a 
game. 
</P>
<P>
	Truth be told, the Braves' heralded pitching staff has been the  
difference in this series, holding New York to five runs in three 
games while the Braves batters have pushed just nine runners 
across. 
</P>
<P>
	Mets pitchers have been good, but the Braves' staff of Greg  
Maddux, Kevin Millwood and Glavine has been great. 
</P>
<P>
	John Olerud is 2-for-11 with no RBIs in the three games, Mike  
Piazza 2-for-11 with one RBI. Robin Ventura is 0-for-9 with no 
RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
	During the regular season, the trio combined to drive in 340  
runs, an average of more than two a game. 
</P>
<P>
	That doesn't mean much to Leiter now. He gave up the unearned  
run, mainly because he walked Gerald Williams leading off the game 
and then threw away Bret Boone's comebacker. 
</P>
<P>
	That may be the hardest thing to live with. He had no problems  
with throws to the plate, just to first base. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
