<HEADLINE> Canucks' Snow Fractures Finger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	VANCOUVER, British Columbia (AP) -- Garth Snow, the Vancouver  
Canucks' top goaltender, is out indefinitely with a fractured index 
finger on his blocking hand, the team announced prior to Friday's 
game against the Carolina Hurricanes. 
</P>
<P>
	Snow was injured during Wednesday's 4-3 overtime loss to the  
Calgary Flames. Snow finished the game, stopping 22 shots. It was 
only his second appearance of the season after missing the first 
two games with a groin injury. 
</P>
<P>
	Backup goalie Kevin Weekes started against the Hurricanes, while  
the Canucks called up Alfie Michaud from their American Hockey 
League affiliate, the Syracuse Crunch. Michaud, last spring's Final 
Four MVP after leading Maine to the NCAA championship, has a 1-2 
record and 2.36 goals-against average with the Crunch. 
  	   	
